<p>Reports Spring <code>&lt;bean&gt;</code> using constructor-based dependency injection.</p>

<p>The inspection triggers when it can't find an appropriate constructor or factory method for <code>&lt;bean&gt;</code> with the configured
<code>&lt;constructor-arg&gt;</code> tags and defined <code>autowire</code> policy.</p>

<p><b>Example:</b></p>
<pre><code lang="java">
    public class MyComponent {
    // constructor
    public MyComponent(MyBean bean) {}
    // factory method
    public static MyComponent getInstance(String name, int port) {
    }
</code></pre>
<pre><code lang="xml">
    &lt;beans&gt;
      &lt;bean class="beans.MyComponent" id="foo"&gt; &lt;!-- reports "No matching constructor found in class 'MyComponent" --&gt;
         &lt;constructor-arg ref="myBean"/&gt;
         &lt;constructor-arg value="123"/&gt;
      &lt;/bean&gt;

      &lt;bean class="beans.MyComponent" factory-method="getInstance"&gt; &lt;!-- reports "No matching factory method found in class" --&gt;
         &lt;constructor-arg value="123"/&gt;
      &lt;/bean&gt;
    &lt;/beans&gt;
</code></pre>
</body>
